# .trivyignore
# Deliberate suppressions for findings that are accepted risks in this repository.
# Each entry must include a justification comment explaining the decision.
#
# Format:
#   AVD-ID [exp:YYYY-MM-DD]
#   # Justification
#
# Docs: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# AWS-0104 – Security group egress unrestricted to 0.0.0.0/0
# Resource: aws_vpc_security_group_egress_rule.all_outbound (network/security_groups.tf)
# Justification: The core-default-sg is a shared baseline SG for internal VPC workloads.
# Outbound traffic is intentionally unrestricted at the SG level; network-level egress
# control is enforced via the NACL (network/vpc.tf) which restricts egress to
# TCP 443, TCP/UDP 53, TCP 80, and ephemeral return ports only.
AVD-AWS-0104
